    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Yeah, I'll check the connection pool. I also checked the logs for any specific error codes around those time windows, but there's nothing but the timeout. It just feels so erratic, like something is just causing a momentary hitch for no logical reason. Any other ideas for what could cause that kind of unpredictable, \"ghost in the machine\" behavior?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "\"Ghost in the machine\" behavior like this often suggests a non-deterministic failure mode, which can be tricky to track down. It's less likely to be a clean application bug and more likely related to infrastructure or external dependencies. I would check for garbage collection pauses in your application instances, as a long GC pause can cause threads to freeze momentarily, mimicking a service outage. Furthermore, look into any autoscaling events or health check cycles happening on the underlying hosts during those spike times, as these can introduce brief periods of instability.",
      "source": "target",
